.TH LPF-SYSCTL 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.3" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-sysctl \- check or diff kernel sysctl parameters
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf sysctl <check|diff>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Check or diff kernel sysctl parameters required by lpf.
check mode reads required sysctls from /proc/sys and prints key=value pairs.
diff mode snapshots observed sysctls and diffs them against the required set.
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf sysctl check
lpf sysctl diff
.SH FILES
/proc/sys
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-apply(8), sysctl(8)
